LAGOS – After Rivers United beat Bloemfontein Celtic 2-0 away in the first leg of their CAF Confederation Cup first round tie on Wednesday, the club is now N2.4m richer courtesy of the promise of the owner of Nigeria Na­tional League (NNL) side Go Round FC Felix Obuah. Obuah, before the match on Wednesday in South Af­rica, promised Rivers Unit­ed the sum of Two Million Naira (N2m) if they beat their opponent. Should the match end in a draw, the former People’s Democratic Party (PDP) chairman in Rivers State has also pledged One Million Naira (N1m) to the team, with an additional Two Hundred Thousand Naira (N200,000) for each goal they score against Celtic. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The team did not only win but scored two goals in the process. Second-half goals from Godwin Aguda and Fortune Omoniwari ensured that the Port Harcourt-based side is in the driver’s seat in this contest. 68 Domestic Sponsors Agree To Extend Contracts For Postponed Tokyo Games Ilaji Hotels Set To Host WBF Title Fight Aguda was on target in the 70th minute and 10 min­utes afterward, Omoniwari doubled the advantage and also sealed the victory. However, the General Manager of the team Chief Dr Okey Kpalukwu has con­gratulated the players and the technical crew for the win. “You have raised the Ni­gerian flag high” he said in a statement. “I congratulate the play­ers and technical crew led by Stanley Eguma for doing us proud. The Austin Festus-led team flew the flag of our nation proudly both in and out of field. “They gave out their all. We congratulate them for not let­ting Rivers State, our number one supporter The Executive Governor of Rivers State, His Excellency, Nyesom Ezenwo Wike and Nigeria down.” Kpalukwu also commend­ed Bro Felix Obuah for the promise to reward the team with two million Naira for a win and two hundred thou­sand